Installation and Setup usbguardnotifier

To install USBGuard Notifier, follow these steps:

    Install USBGuard and the notifier:
        For Debian-based systems: apt install usbguard usbguard-notifier
        For Fedora-based systems: dnf install usbguard usbguard-notifier

    Start the USBGuard service:
        Use systemctl enable --now usbguard.service to enable and start the service.

    Configure user permissions for notifications:
        Allow specific users to listen to device signals using commands like:
            sudo usbguard add-user USER -d listen
            sudo usbguard add-user -g GROUP -d listen

    Start the notifier service:
        Run systemctl start --user usbguard-notifier.service to initiate the notifier.

